    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:space="preserve" xml:lang="grc" resp="#AA">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/>θεοῖς πᾶσι
                    <lb n="2"/>σωτῆρσιν
                    <lb n="3"/>Γόργον
                    <lb n="4"/>καὶ
                    <lb n="5"/>οἱ ἄλλοι <expan><abbr>πολῖ</abbr><ex>ται</ex></expan>
                </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus">
                <listApp><app><note>Korhonen 2004</note></app></listApp>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" xml:lang="en" resp="#AA">
                <p>To all the deliverer Gods. Gorgon and the other citizens.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>Although originally believed by Korhonen 2004 to be an imperial Roman archaising text, Korhonen 2018 provides convincing arguments and explanations for believing this to be a later 18th century creation.</p>
            </div>
